CEZ Aims to Have 3,000 Megawatts of Renewables Abroad by 2016

-- B y   L a d k a   B a u e r o v a
-- 
2011-10-11T07:37:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/cez-aims-to-have-3-000-megawatts-of-renewables-abroad-by-2016.html
CEZ AS (CEZ) , the  Czech Republic ’s largest
power producer, aims to have 3,000 megawatts in renewable-energy
projects abroad by 2016, foreign division director Tomas Pleskac 
said today at a press conference in Prague.  CEZ will focus on building wind farms in  Poland ,  Romania  
and  Germany , Pleskac said. The company doesn’t plan any
offshore projects, he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ladka Bauerova at 
 lbauerova@bloomberg.net  